      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE FINANCE COMMITTEE AND THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS THE FORM 990.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>EMPLOYEES ARE EXPECTED TO USE GOOD JUDGMENT, TO ADHERE TO HIGH ETHICAL STANDARDS, AND TO AVOID SITUATIONS THAT CREATE AN ACTUAL OR POTENTIAL CONFLICT BETWEEN THEIR PERSONAL INTERESTS AND THE INTERESTS OF THE COMPANY. EMPLOYEES UNSURE AS TO WHETHER A CERTAIN TRANSACTION, ACTIVITY, OR RELATIONSHIP CONSTITUTES A CONFLICT OF INTEREST SHOULD DISCUSS IT WITH THEIR IMMEDIATE SUPERVISOR OR THE HUMAN RESOURCES DEPARTMENT FOR CLARIFICATION. ANY EXCEPTIONS TO THIS GUIDELINE MUST BE APPROVED IN WRITING BY THE COMPANY'S CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER. EMPLOYEES SHOULD BE AWARE THAT IF THEY ENTER INTO A PERSONAL RELATIONSHIP WITH A SUBORDINATE EMPLOYEE OR WITH AN EMPLOYEE OF A COMPETITOR, SUPPLIER, OR CUSTOMER, A CONFLICT OF INTEREST MAY EXIST, WHICH REQUIRES FULL DISCLOSURE TO THE COMPANY. EMPLOYEES ARE PROHIBITED FROM SOCIALIZING, OTHER THAN WORK-RELATED ACTIVITIES, OR DATING CUSTOMERS OR CLIENTS WHILE THE CUSTOMERS OR CLIENTS ARE RECEIVING SERVICES FROM CRP OR AFTER IF IT IS REASONABLY PROBABLE THAT THE CUSTOMER OR CLIENT WILL RECEIVE SERVICES FROM CRP IN THE FUTURE. FAILURE TO ADHERE TO THIS GUIDELINE, INCLUDING FAILURE TO DISCLOSE ANY CONFLICTS OR TO SEEK AN EXCEPTION, MAY RESULT IN DISCIPLINARY ACTION, UP TO AND INCLUDING TERMINATION OF EMPLOYMENT.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE PAY SCALE FOR ALL EMPLOYEES, INCLUDING THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND CFO WAS DETERMINED AFTER CONSULTING SEVERAL OUTSIDE SOURCES FOR COMPARABILITY. A STEP-IN-COLUMN WAS APPROVED BY THE BOARD. ANNUAL ADJUSTMENTS TO THE PAY SCALE ARE APPROVED BY BOARD ACTION.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO ALL FUNDING SOURCES AND POTENTIAL FUNDING SOURCES UPON REQUEST.</ExplanationTxt>
